2. Sprint retrospective [https://www.notion.so/Week-6-4359320eb407461eaadf58bef63f949a?pvs=4](https://www.notion.so/Week-6-4359320eb407461eaadf58bef63f949a?pvs=21)
3. Discuss the results of usability tests and what do we agree to improve.

Users were put into complete black box scenario. After short instructions they improved a lot.

Results:

![Untitled](https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/secure.notion-static.com/16398bbd-e7f5-49af-97ae-8d6006c10694/Untitled.png)

![Untitled](https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/secure.notion-static.com/e70cd794-c318-4c8c-95f4-7bce9ddea6b8/Untitled.png)

1. Trigger node:
    1. It is not clear that it is also a start node - rename it, and preferably put it in the graph by default.
2. Adding and connecting edges and nodes:
    1. Users would like a functionality to add nodes by clicking them or dragging - the nodes in scrollbar look like buttons.
    2. It is not clear how to delete or add an edge.
    3. It would be more intuitive if adding new nodes would be done in “add to already existing node manner”.
    4. Or maybe add a starting point for the edge to connect.
3. We should add some kind of functionality for the users to execute the graph from graph builder.
4. We miss a message that inform that saving of a graph wasn’t successful.
5. Difference between ‘save’ and ‘save as draft’ is not clear to the users.
6. Improve node info - preferably add names, because reference is not clear enough. Also maybe show the data that the node stores.
7. Improve the layout of buttons used in the node editor - bigger button should draw more attention

![Untitled](https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/secure.notion-static.com/7474d1c4-a651-45cd-a495-774371b4e73e/Untitled.png)

1. Condition nodes:
    1. The description in the filter node was not clear. Names are not specific enough.
    2. Filter is heavy - a lot of info
2. Action nodes:
    1. Description for passing the data into body was not clear.
    2. Description of what argument is wasn't clear.
    3. Forgot to add argument after entering it to Json body. - maybe some kind of check to prevent this.
3. User clicked on "edit" while trying to connect the nodes.
4. User confused "add argument button.
5. User didn't know the proper format of JSON.
6. Some sort of debugger - step by step what data is stored inside each node.
7. Rename arguments or think about description
8. Users didn’t always save changes. Maybe a pop out?

![Untitled](https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/secure.notion-static.com/7dc87a79-998a-496e-b6c6-9063bb28f9e2/Untitled.png)

1. Accidently deleted a node
2. Time zone for trigger node
3. Make selecting the parent more explicit

