## Notes

- we only got 10 responses but it was enough to get some very concrete and useful feedback
- going over the forms and what tasks we did
- most important points on the user tests and the received feedback
    - loading screen
    - page for new graph creation feels empty, too much negative space
    - observation: users were seeing the application for the first time, but they got noticeably better at using the application over time
    - not clear that the **trigger** is a start node! the solution we liked is to have the trigger node in the graph by default
    - nodes look like buttons! **users tried to click the nodes** instead of drag and dropping
    - not clear how to **delete or add an edge** at first; maybe add a separate button for adding and clicking to delete
    - adding nodes should potentially be different: always appending new nodes to an existing graph instead of adding nodes and then connecting them
    - it should be possible to execute the graph from the builder!
    - the **forms** have a lot of text, difficult to understand at a glance.
    - pop up about unsaved changes when leaving the graph editor
    - accidental **deletion**, button easy to miss-click
    - **labels** not very intuitive, maybe change the names
    - time zones for trigger schedule potentially: at least specify which time zone we are using, then users can adjust on their own
- good to prioritise things which are impossible to recover from, like node deletion, since having that be unintuitive could be very frustrating
- summary of what we did this week and retrospective conclusions, showcase of test coverage reports

### Github

- time estimates and weights a bit inconsistent, try to work on this
- we should go back and try to improve the previous issues
- if we have some sort of rule for assigning weights then we should make it explicit and put it into the code of conduct or report